"1. Load MovieLens 100K from ./u.data using tab separation and preserve the original user and item IDs throughout the entire pipeline.\n2. Convert ratings to implicit positives by keeping only interactions with rating > 3 and dropping all others before any splitting.\n3. Apply iterative 5-core filtering on the positive interactions until convergence so every remaining user and every remaining item has at least 5 interactions.\n4. Use the filtered dataset as the sole source for all later steps; do not remap or inconsistently alter IDs between filtering, splitting, training, recommendation, and evaluation.\n5. Run exactly 3 independent experiment repetitions with 3 distinct random seeds, and explicitly set both numpy.random and Python random seeds for each repetition.\n6. For each seed, create a fresh user-based 80/20 holdout split from the filtered data, assigning about 20% of each eligible user\u2019s interactions to test and the rest to train.\n7. Skip any user that cannot support a valid split, and define evaluable users as users with both nonempty train and nonempty test interactions after splitting.\n8. Ensure each seed uses its own independently sampled split and trains a fresh model only on that seed\u2019s training interactions.\n9. Use LensKit 0.14.4 ImplicitMF with ALS and default hyperparameters only; do not manually tune model settings.\n10. Generate top-10 recommendations for all evaluable users in a single batch recommend call rather than looping over users individually.\n11. Exclude each user\u2019s training items from that user\u2019s candidate set so already-seen items are never recommended.\n12. Evaluate recommendations at cutoff 10 using per-user nDCG@10 and Precision@10 computed against that seed\u2019s held-out positive test items.\n13. Compute the mean nDCG@10 and mean Precision@10 across evaluable users separately for each seed.\n14. Aggregate the 3 per-seed metric values into overall mean and sample standard deviation for both nDCG@10 and Precision@10.\n15. Save one CSV file in the working directory containing one row per seed plus one aggregate row with the computed metrics.\n16. Print the aggregated mean and standard deviation for both metrics to stdout.\n17. Make the script fully reproducible and self-contained so it runs without errors in the working directory assuming LensKit 0.14.4 and the MovieLens 100K u.data file are available."